The better your idea is -- and I do think this was a good one -- the more I should think you'd want to bring solvers directly into the trick.  Make it necessary for them to "match wits with you", as it were.  Not just sit back and admire your grid after they've completed the puzzle.

That's the way I'm always thinking when I'm trying to dream up a puzzle theme.  How much will there be for the solver to actually DO?  Will HE have to be clever?  Will SHE have to be resourceful?  I don't always succeed to the full extent I'm striving for, but that's my intended goal.

